    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-07-31T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-07-31T17:00:00-05:00" n="437"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d437">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.94/1621a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Consul at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Butrick</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-07-31T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 31, 1940—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>335. Wireless to the <hi rend="italic">New York Times</hi> under Shanghai date
                    line July 31 contains a statement that “it was reported that several of the
                    Japanese agency offices in Shanghai late yesterday received cabled orders from
                    the head offices in Tokyo to stress anti-American features in news items from
                    China”.</p>
                <p>The Department would appreciate receiving by radio such pertinent information
                    with regard to this statement as you may be able readily to obtain, together
                    with your comment with regard thereto.</p>
                <p>Sent to Shanghai. Repeated to Peiping and Chungking.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
